// no-raw-html-interactive-element — UI primitives discipline enforcement.
//
// Forbids raw JSX `<button>`, `<input>`, `<textarea>`, `<select>` inside
// `packages/{app,desktop,plugin}/src/**/*.tsx`. Consumers must use the
// shadcn primitives (`Button`, `Input`, `Textarea`, `Select`) from
// `@/components/ui/*`. If the component isn't installed yet, add it via
// `bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <name>` first — never roll your own.
//
// The editor subtree (`packages/app/src/editor/**`) is exempt at the
// Biome `overrides[].includes[]` layer because ProseMirror NodeViews and
// PM-managed views legitimately render raw HTML for measurement / chrome
// reasons (see `biome.jsonc` for the scope; the `useSemanticElements` and
// related a11y suppressions in editor/* are part of the same exemption).
//
// Why a GritQL plugin and not Biome's built-in `a11y/useButtonType` or
// `useSemanticElements`: those address a11y semantics, not the
// shadcn-first design contract. The team's specific failure mode (see
// PR #937) was Codex / Claude-Code / human contributors writing raw
// `<button>` JSX while a shadcn `<Button>` from `@/components/ui/button`
// already existed in the file — an a11y-clean violation of the
// shadcn-first contract. This rule is the structural enforcement that
// catches it at editor-save / `bun run lint` time.
//
// Suppress narrow legitimate uses (e.g. a checkbox display in a slash
// menu where shadcn `Checkbox` would over-style) with:
//   // biome-ignore lint/plugin/no-raw-html-interactive-element: <reason>
//
// For larger backlogs (files that pre-date the rule and need migration),
// use the file-level form at the top of the file:
//   // biome-ignore-all lint/plugin/no-raw-html-interactive-element: <reason>
//
// See PRECEDENTS.md #42 (custom Biome enforcement is GritQL plugins).

language js

or {
    `<button $...>$...</button>` as $node,
    `<button $.../>` as $node,
    `<input $.../>` as $node,
    `<input $...></input>` as $node,
    `<textarea $...>$...</textarea>` as $node,
    `<textarea $.../>` as $node,
    `<select $...>$...</select>` as $node,
    `<select $.../>` as $node
} where {
    register_diagnostic(
        span = $node,
        message = "Raw HTML interactive primitive — use shadcn Button/Input/Textarea/Select from @/components/ui/* (install missing via `bunx --bun shadcn@latest add <name>`). See https://github.com/inkeep/open-knowledge/blob/main/biome-plugins/README.md#no-raw-html-interactive-elementgrit"
    )
}
